&lt;p&gt;The General Assembly is the primary decision-making body of the GPCA and consists of delegates from each active county organization. Delegates are selected by the counties each July and serve as delegates to both the GA and the Online GA (the SGA). &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GPCA Committees, Working Groups and County Organizations wishing to submit agenda items should notify the State Meeting Planning Committee &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:agenda-team@cagreens.org&quot;&gt;(agenda-team@cagreens.org)&lt;/a&gt; by March 11th and submit final text &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cagreens.org/ga/proposal-format&quot;&gt;in this format&lt;/a&gt; by March 22nd. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions please send them to &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:agenda-team@cagreens.org&quot;&gt;agenda-team@cagreens.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
